# API Route Conventions

- Use `ok(data)` and `err(message, status)` from `@/lib/api` for all responses — never build JSON manually
- Import `db` from `@/lib/db` — never create a new database connection
- Validate enums using `CATEGORIES`, `SEVERITIES`, `STATUSES` from `@/lib/api` with `.includes()`
- Always use parameterized SQL queries (`?` placeholders) — never interpolate user input
- After INSERT or UPDATE, re-SELECT and return the full row via `ok()`
- For dynamic route params in Next.js 16: `{ params }: { params: Promise<{ id: string }> }` — await it
- Pagination: default `page=1`, `limit=50`, cap limit at 200

See `app/api/CLAUDE.md` for detailed patterns and examples.
